honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class SensorCalibration_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.SensorCalibration_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SensorCalibration_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the sensor calibration data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    RVBlack Mark paper Value
    GRBlack Mark Sensor Gain
    MVBlack Mark Value
    SGGap Sensor Gain
    SGTGap Sensor Gain should be used with Thermal Transfer Media
    GMGap Mark level
    GMTGap Mark level should be used with Thermal Transfer Media
    PVPaper Level
    PVTPaper Level should be used with Thermal Transfer Media
    PGPresenter Sensor Gain
    EVSensor Clear Value
    EVTSensor Clear Value should be used with Thermal Transfer Media
    ACAuto Calibration Mode
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • SensorCalibration_DPL

        public SensorCalibration_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
